(Bulou, 1982) identify three phases of RbAlF$_{4}$: \begin{itemize} \item Above 553K RbAlF$_{4}$ I has the tetragonal \href{current_web_home_dir/AB4C_tP6_123_b_eg_c-001}{TlAlF$_{4}$ ($H0_{8}$) structure}. \item Between 282 and 553K RbAlF$_{4}$ II is tetragonal, \href{current_web_home_dir/AB4C_tP12_127_a_eg_c-001}{space group $P4/mbm$ \#127}. \item Below 282K RbAlF$_{4}$ III is orthorhombic, space group $Pmmn$ \#59 (this structure). \end{itemize} ~ \vspace{-.25in} 
 The different structures are distinguished by the tilt of the AlF$_{6}$ octahedra. 
 We use Bulou and Nouet's data for RbAlF$_{4}$ III at 5K.
